__init__(string).details: To omit the opcodes for checking the `msg.value` in the creation-time EVM bytecode, the constructor is declared as `payable`.

params.base_uri_: The maximum 80-character user-readable string base URI for computing `uri`.

balanceOf(address,uint256).details: Returns the amount of tokens of token type `id` owned by `owner`.

returns._0: uint256 The 32-byte token amount owned by `owner`.
DynArray The 32-byte array of token amounts owned by `owners`.

burn(address,uint256,uint256).details: Destroys `amount` tokens of token type `id` from `owner`.

params.amount: The 32-byte token amount to be destroyed.

params.amounts: The 32-byte array of token amounts that are being destroyed. Note that the order and length must match the 32-byte `ids` array.
params.ids: The 32-byte array of token identifiers. Note that the order and length must match the 32-byte `amounts` array.

exists(uint256).details: Indicates whether any token exist with a given `id` or not.

returns._0: bool The verification whether `id` exists or not.

renounce_ownership().details: Leaves the contract without an owner.

params.amounts: The 32-byte array of token amounts that are being transferred. Note that the order and length must match the 32-byte `ids` array.
params.data: The maximum 1,024-byte additional data with no specified format.
params.ids: The 32-byte array of token identifiers. Note that the order and length must match the 32-byte `amounts` array.
params.owner: The 20-byte address which previously owned the token.

safeTransferFrom(address,address,uint256.details: Transfers `amount` tokens of token type `id` from `owner` to `to`.

params.amount: The 32-byte token amount that is being transferred.
params.data: The maximum 1,024-byte additional data with no specified format.
params.owner: The 20-byte address which previously owned the token.

safe_mint(address,uint256,uint256,bytes).details: Safely mints `amount` tokens of token type `id` and transfers them to `owner`.

params.amount: The 32-byte token amount to be created.
params.data: The maximum 1,024-byte additional data with no specified format.

params.amounts: The 32-byte array of token amounts that are being created. Note that the order and length must match the 32-byte `ids` array.
params.data: The maximum 1,024-byte additional data with no specified format.
params.ids: The 32-byte array of token identifiers. Note that the order and length must match the 32-byte `amounts` array.

setApprovalForAll(address,bool).details: Grants or revokes permission to `operator` to transfer the caller's tokens, according to `approved`.

params.approved: The Boolean variable that sets the approval status.

set_minter(address,bool).details: Adds or removes an address `minter` to/from the list of allowed minters. Note that only the `owner` can add or remove `minter` addresses. Also, the `minter` cannot be the zero address. Eventually, the `owner` cannot remove himself from the list of allowed minters.

params.status: The Boolean variable that sets the status.

set_uri(uint256,string).details: Sets the Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) for token type `id`.

params.token_uri: The maximum 432-character user-readable string URI for computing `uri`.

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: Returns `True` if this contract implements the interface defined by `interface_id`.

returns._0: bool The verification whether the contract implements the interface or not.

transfer_ownership(address).details: Transfers the ownership of the contract to a new account `new_owner`.

params.new_owner: The 20-byte address of the new owner.

uri(uint256).details: Returns the Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) for token type `id`.

params.id: The 32-byte identifier of the token type `id`.

returns._0: String The maximum 512-character user-readable string token URI of the token type `id`.

devdoc.title: Modern and Gas-Efficient ERC-1155 Implementation

balanceOf(address,uint256).notice: Note that `owner` cannot be the zero address.

balanceOfBatch(address[],uint256[]).notice: Note that `owners` and `ids` must have the same length.

burn(address,uint256,uint256).notice: Note that `owner` cannot be the zero address. Also, `owner` must have at least `amount` tokens of token type `id`.

burn_batch(address,uint256[],uint256[]).notice: Note that `ids` and `amounts` must have the same length.

renounce_ownership().notice: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner. Note that the `owner` is also removed from the list of allowed minters. WARNING: All other existing `minter` addresses will still be able to create new tokens. Consider removing all non-owner minter addresses first via `set_minter` before calling `renounce_ownership`.

safeBatchTransferFrom(address,address,ui.notice: Note that `ids` and `amounts` must have the same length. Also, if `to` refers to a smart contract, it must implement {IERC1155Receiver-onERC1155BatchReceived} and return the acceptance magic value. WARNING: This function can potentially allow a reentrancy attack when transferring tokens to an untrusted contract, when invoking {IERC1155Receiver-onERC1155BatchReceived} on the receiver. We ensure that we consistently follow the checks-effects-interactions (CEI) pattern to avoid being vulnerable to this type of attack.

safeTransferFrom(address,address,uint256.notice: Note that `to` cannot be the zero address. Also, if the caller is not `owner`, it must have been approved to spend `owner`'s tokens via `setApprovalForAll`. Furthermore, `owner` must have a balance of tokens of type `id` of at least `amount`. Eventually, if `to` refers to a smart contract, it must implement {IERC1155Receiver-onERC1155Received} and return the acceptance magic value. WARNING: This function can potentially allow a reentrancy attack when transferring tokens to an untrusted contract, when invoking {IERC1155Receiver-onERC1155Received} on the receiver. We ensure that we consistently follow the checks- effects-interactions (CEI) pattern to avoid being vulnerable to this type of attack.

safe_mint(address,uint256,uint256,bytes).notice: Only authorised minters can access this function. Note that `owner` cannot be the zero address. Also, if `owner` refers to a smart contract, it must implement {IERC1155Receiver-onERC1155Received}, which is called upon a safe transfer.

safe_mint_batch(address,uint256[],uint25.notice: Note that `ids` and `amounts` must have the same length. Also, if `owner` refers to a smart contract, it must implement {IERC1155Receiver-onERC1155BatchReceived}, which is called upon a safe transfer.

setApprovalForAll(address,bool).notice: Note that `operator` cannot be the caller.

set_uri(uint256,string).notice: This function is decoupled from `safe_mint` and `safe_mint_batch`, as multiple of the same `id` can be minted. However, the permissions are shared with `is_minter`. Only minters have the authorisation to change token URIs.

transfer_ownership(address).notice: Note that this function can only be called by the current `owner`. Also, the `new_owner` cannot be the zero address. WARNING: The ownership transfer also removes the previous owner's minter role and assigns the minter role to `new_owner` accordingly.

uri(uint256).notice: If the `{id}` substring is present in the URI, it must be replaced by clients with the actual token type ID. Note that the `uri` function must not be used to check for the existence of a token as it is possible for the implementation to return a valid string even if the token does not exist.

userdoc.notice: These functions implement the ERC-1155 standard interface: - https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-1155. In addition, the following functions have been added for convenience: - `uri` (`external` `view` function), - `set_uri` (`external` function), - `total_supply` (`external` `view` function), - `exists` (`external` `view` function), - `burn` (`external` function), - `burn_batch` (`external` function), - `is_minter` (`external` `view` function), - `safe_mint` (`external` function), - `safe_mint_batch` (`external` function), - `set_minter` (`external` function), - `owner` (`external` `view` function), - `transfer_ownership` (`external` function), - `renounce_ownership` (`external` function), - `_check_on_erc1155_received` (`internal` function), - `_check_on_erc1155_batch_received` (`internal` function), - `_before_token_transfer` (`internal` function), - `_after_token_transfer` (`internal` function). The implementation is inspired by OpenZeppelin's implementation here: https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/master/contracts/token/ERC1155/ERC1155.sol.
